onyomiExamples.meaning: year, counter for years (e.g. of an era), grades (e.g. school), period of an apprentice's contract (usu. ten years)
years gone by, earlier years, former years, the past
non-leap year, normal year (esp. as pertains to weather patterns, vegetative growth, harvest yields, etc.)

kunyomiExamples.meaning: year, age, years, past one's prime, old age
beginning of the year, early in the New Year
mature age, advanced age, maturity, age when one is old enough to know better
